From 3ddf405cc3696fb83cf3dac0849e940e8fba51c2 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Panoptic <panoptic@localhost>
Date: Thu, 5 Mar 2026 09:32:15 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Replace PCRE with Vectorscan + PCRE2 for service
 fingerprinting
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Swap out the legacy PCRE (end-of-life since 2020) regex engine with
Vectorscan (Hyperscan-compatible) for multi-pattern scanning and PCRE2
for selective capture-group extraction.

Architecture (Option 3 — Vectorscan + PCRE2 selective fallback):

  - All service/client signatures are compiled into a single Vectorscan
    block-mode multi-pattern database per category (serv_tcp, serv_udp,
    client_tcp, client_udp).  This replaces the O(N) linear pcre_exec
    walk with a single DFA pass over all patterns simultaneously.

  - Signatures that use capture groups ($1/$2 in title templates) also
    get a PCRE2 compiled pattern.  After Vectorscan identifies which
    pattern matched, one targeted pcre2_match extracts the captures.

  - Signatures with unsupported Vectorscan constructs (negative
    lookaheads, backreferences) are compiled in HS_FLAG_PREFILTER mode.
    Prefilter matches are confirmed by a single PCRE2 exec.

  - Signatures that cannot compile in Vectorscan at all (extremely rare)
    fall back to linear PCRE2 scanning.

Performance impact for ~3000 pattern fingerprint libraries:

  Before: Up to 3000 sequential pcre_exec() calls per payload
  After:  1 hs_scan() + at most 1 pcre2_match() per payload

  First-match-wins ordering is preserved by sorting Vectorscan match
  IDs by their original signature ordinal.

Safety considerations:

  - Eliminates libpcre (EOL) from the attack surface on sensors
    deployed in hospitals and government networks
  - PCRE2 is actively maintained and receives CVE patches
  - Graceful degradation: patterns that fail Vectorscan compilation
    fall through to prefilter, then PCRE2-only, with logging at each
    stage
  - Memory cleanup ordering ensures Vectorscan databases are freed
    before the signature linked-lists they reference

Build changes:

  - src/Makefile: -lpcre replaced with -lhs -lpcre2-8 -lstdc++ -lm
  - CMakeLists.txt: new CMake build system alongside existing Makefile
  - Dependencies: libvectorscan-dev (or libhyperscan-dev) + libpcre2-dev

New files:
  - src/hs_engine.h  — Vectorscan engine data structures and API
  - src/hs_engine.c  — Multi-pattern compilation, scanning, app-name
                       extraction with PCRE2 capture support
  - CMakeLists.txt   — Modern build system with pkg-config detection

Modified files:
  - src/prads.h      — signature struct: pcre* -> pcre2_code* + hs fields
  - src/config.h     — globalconfig: added hs_sigdb_t* per category
  - src/servicefp/servicefp.c — deferred regex compilation, PCRE2 cleanup
  - src/servicefp/tcps.c      — Vectorscan scan + PCRE2 capture path
  - src/servicefp/tcpc.c      — same
  - src/servicefp/udps.c      — same
  - src/prads.c      — init/cleanup for Vectorscan databases
